Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows two sides with each one basketry coil, suggesting that the piece was attached between the lid and the wall of a basket. The front shows a small oval scarab-like seal-impression. The motif shows a circumferential line, inside a kneeling figure, facing to the left, in front of it a vertical cartouche with a kheper as lowest sign. The impression is not very clear. Finger impressions under the seal-impression.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
